Program: The Documentary
Title: New York's Catholics
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0092pvm
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 22 Aug 2010
The religious face of New York is being transformed. Once the preserve of the Irish Catholics, New York's churches are now filled with Hispanic Catholics. The dominance of the Irish immigrant community has long been on the wane - but not so the Irish leadership of the Catholic Church, which is still led by an Irish American Archbishop. Maurice Walsh travels to New York to talk to Catholics about the leaders of their community. Show less